    "body": "# Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n\n\n## Purpose\nAdd FP4 gemms from FlashInfer as backends.\n\nIf FlashInfer is available, defaults to FlashInfer cutlass kernels because testing on Llama3 ISL=OSL=1024 max_num_batched_tokens=8192 concurrency=128 shows that it is always faster than alternatives.\n\nTime of original vLLM cutlass kernels vs FlashInfer cutlass kernels in gen-only phase in μs:\nfc_qkv: 21.3 vs 14.8\nfc_out: 15.1 vs 13.7\nfc13: 76.9 vs 53.1\nfc2: 42.3 vs 32.6\n\nTime of original vLLM cutlass kernels vs FlashInfer cutlass kernels in ctx/gen phase in μs:\nfc_qkv: 470.9 vs 220.2\nfc_out: 388.5 vs 176.5\nfc13: 3293.1 vs 1192.1\nfc2: 1178.7 vs 639.6\n\nFlashInfer trtllm-gen kernels are also added but only enabled through `envs.VLLM_USE_TRTLLM_FP4_GEMM`.\nThey are expected to have better perf in min-latency scenarios but more investigation is needed.\n\nI'm not sure if I'm using vLLM's custom op registration wrong, but I couldn't get it to work. I used `@torch.library.custom_op` for now, will investigate to confirm.\n\n## Test Plan\n\n## Test Result\n\n## (Optional) Documentation Update\n\n",
